{{Infobox musical artist |image = |image_size = |background = non_vocal_instrumentalist |birth_date = {{birth year and age|1978}} |origin = [[Tehran]], [[Iran]] |instrument = [[Dayereh]], [[Daf]] |genre = [[Persian traditional music]] |occupation = [[Composer]] |years_active = 1998–present }}
'''Sara Ahmadi''' ({{lang-fa|سارا احمدی}}) (born 19 March 1978 in [[Tehran]]) is an [[Iranian peoples|Iranian]] [[daf]] and [[dayereh]] player and the lead composer of [[Kaliveh Group]].<ref>[http://www.tavoosonline.com/News/NewsDetailEn.aspx?src=20656 Simin Ghanem singing her new songs at Rudaki Hall]</ref> She is the sister of [[Asieh Ahmadi]].<ref>[http://europe.newsweek.com/how-america-used-banjo-diplomacy-soothe-iran-330272 How America used banjo diplomacy to soothe Iran]</ref><ref>[http://asalmalekzadeh.ir/ Asal Malekzade]</ref><ref>[http://www.kalivehmusic.com/main/index.php/fa/zendeginevesht-fa/28-sara-ahmadi Ahmadi's Life]</ref>
Ahmadi has made numerous recordings with prominent musicians including [[Simin Ghanem]] and is a member of the [[Rastak Group]], with which she has participated in numerous concerts in Germany, France, Italy, Spain, and the Netherlands. She has also performed at the [[Nations Music Conference]] held in the United States and Japan.<ref>[http://www.theculturist.com/home/a-single-flower-by-kiavash-teymourian-and-sara-ahmadi.html A Single Flower by Kiavash Teymourian and Sara Ahmadi]</ref><ref>[http://mevlana.lv/en/afisha/13 Concert - Charming sounds of the Orient]</ref>
