{{nihongo|'''University of Miyazaki'''|宮崎大学|Miyazaki Daigaku}} is a [[Japanese national university|national university]] in [[Miyazaki, Miyazaki|Miyazaki]], [[Miyazaki Prefecture]], [[Japan]]. The predecessor of the school was founded in 1884, and it was chartered as a university in 2003.<ref name="history">{{Cite web |url=http://www.miyazaki-u.ac.jp/english/contents/about_uom/history.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=2016-08-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160821210623/http://www.miyazaki-u.ac.jp/english/contents/about_uom/history.html |archive-date=2016-08-21 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> The university has undergraduate faculties in education and culture, medicine, engineering, and agriculture.<ref name="faculties">http://www.miyazaki-u.ac.jp/english/contents/school_institutes_faculty/index.html</ref> The university also has a graduate program in medicine and veterinary medicine, as well as a graduate program in agriculture and engineering.<ref name="faculties">http://www.miyazaki-u.ac.jp/english/contents/school_institutes_faculty/index.html</ref>
